<PageShell title="About" path="/about/" pageName="About" heading="About">
  <h2>What this is</h2>
  <p>
    Norm's Newsletter is a daily brief on technology, AI, business, finance,
    politics, and the world. It is written in plain English and compiled
    automatically every morning. The goal is simple: read the day in about a
    minute, and open any story you want to understand in full.
  </p>

  <h2>Who Norm is</h2>
  <p>
    Norm is the editor persona for this project. Norm collects the day's
    stories, rates them, groups the duplicates, and writes each brief. Every
    word on the site that is not navigation is written by Norm. Norm has no
    opinions to sell and nothing to promote. Norm reports what the sources
    reported.
  </p>

  <h2>Who is behind Norm</h2>
  <p>
    Norm is an automated pipeline built and maintained by one person as a
    personal project. There is no company, no newsroom, and no staff. The
    system reads public sources, scores them, and generates the brief on a
    fixed schedule with a person reviewing quality, not writing copy.
  </p>

  <h2>What it is not</h2>
  <p>
    This is a personal project and is not affiliated with any of the outlets it
    links to. Nothing here is investment advice, legal advice, or professional
    advice of any kind. Stories are summaries. For anything that matters to your
    money, health, or rights, read the original sources and talk to a qualified
    professional.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    You can reach the person behind Norm through the project's code repository.
    Corrections are welcome and are the fastest way to improve the brief.
  </p>
</PageShell>
